    "body": "## Solution summary\n\nThe work is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\nRestructured `proofs/attempts/singh-anand-2006-pneqnp/` to match the required format per the issue and comment instructions:\n\n### New files added:\n- **`ORIGINAL.md`** — Markdown reconstruction of arXiv:math/0603605, detailing Anand's argument step by step\n- **`ORIGINAL.pdf`** — Downloaded from arXiv\n- **`proof/README.md`** — Explains the forward proof formalization\n- **`proof/lean/SinghAnandProof.lean`** — Lean 4 formalization of Anand's argument (the invalid inference is marked with a comment)\n- **`proof/rocq/SinghAnandProof.v`** — Rocq formalization of same\n- **`refutation/README.md`** — Explains why the proof fails\n- **`refutation/lean/SinghAnandRefutation.lean`** — Lean 4 refutation proving G(x) holds in non-standard models and Anand's claim leads to contradiction\n- **`refutation/rocq/SinghAnandRefutation.v`** — Rocq refutation of same\n\n### Old files removed:\n- `lean/SinghAnand2006.lean` and `rocq/SinghAnand2006.v` (superseded by the structured proof/ and refutation/ layout)\n\n### Also updated:\n- `README.md` — Rewritten to the new structured format with error explanation\n- `ATTEMPTS.md` — Regenerated via `check_attempt_structure.py`\n\n**PR:** https://github.com/konard/p-vs-np/pull/544\n\n---\n*This summary was automatically extracted from the AI working session output.*",
